---
import image1 from "../../../assets/image_1.jpg";
---

<section class="w-full py-24 md:py-32 px-8 md:px-16 lg:px-24 bg-[#f8f9fb]">
  <div class="max-w-[1000px] mx-auto">
    <div class="mb-10">
      <span
        class="block text-[10px] md:text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[0.25em] text-[#3cbce6] uppercase mb-4"
      >
        Core Concept
      </span>
      <h2
        class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-[54px] text-[#1e293b] tracking-tight leading-[1.1]"
        style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;"
      >
        The Weight of Absence
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-20 pl-6 md:pl-8 border-l-[3px] border-[#c2e8f6]">
      <p
        class="text-[17px] md:text-[19px] italic text-[#4b5563] leading-[1.7] max-w-[750px] font-light"
      >
        "A forest is not defined by its trees alone — but by the darkness between them.
        It is in that darkness where roots reach deepest, where what is buried
        becomes the quiet architecture of everything still standing above."
      </p>
    </div>

    <div
      class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[45%_1fr] gap-12 md:gap-16 items-center"
    >
      <div class="w-full aspect-square rounded-sm overflow-hidden bg-slate-200">
        <img
          src={image1.src}
          alt="Light and shadow abstract"
          class="w-full h-full object-cover  hover:opacity-100 hover:scale-105 transition-all duration-700"
        />
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col gap-6">
        <p
          class="text-[#4b5563] text-[15px] md:text-[16px] leading-[1.8] font-light"
        >
          Absence is not failure. It is the deliberate act of knowing what to
          let go — and having the courage to leave the space empty rather than
          fill it with noise that does not belong. De Aurimori is built on what
          was removed, not what was added.
        </p>
        <p
          class="text-[#4b5563] text-[15px] md:text-[16px] leading-[1.8] font-light"
        >
          Every void we leave is a question we trust you to answer yourself.
          Every silence in our work is not an oversight — it is an invitation.
          To pause. To feel the weight of what is no longer there.
          And to understand that some things only become visible once everything
          else has fallen away.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>